      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a deeply complex force, and its impact depends entirely on its manifestation. When it fosters shared civic values and a sense of collective purpose, it can be a powerful engine for social cohesion and national progress. However, when nationalism devolves into chauvinism, xenophobia, and the belief in inherent superiority, it becomes a dangerously divisive ideology that fuels conflict. Therefore, it is a tool whose morality is determined by how it is wielded.",
